<br>
Please mind that: to you give a person limits, is to prevent them from performing their very best potential.<br>
<br>
Giving casters ONLY 30 secs to get ready makes the matches lop sided. For some people, strategic buff placements are vital to success in duels.  Dispell them and give them 5 - 10 mins to get ready.  You can assign another person to watch over another to make sure they don't recieve buffs from other class.<br>
<br>
Not allowing Mez and Fear to be used makes it unfair.  Asking an enchanter not to use Mez is like asking a Wizard to not nuke. These spells are the definition of their class, don't limit their ability, it already happened in BotB.<br>
<br>
Not allowing fighters to step out of the tiled floor, again makes things lop sided.<br>
<br>
I don't know about you, but when I duel someone, I give them all the time they need to buff and get ready.  I don't give them any rules or limits.  This way when I kill them, I can say that I killed you when you tried your very best, which makes my victory much more satisfying.<br>
<br>
<br>
-<br>
Kenkoy Ako [38 Eldritch/Palomides]<br>
